title: Adrian Peterson active for the Vikings against Lions
text:
Adrian Peterson active for the Vikings; Landry Jones makes 1st start for Steelers By The Associated Press   12:46 pmLast   12:47 pm   
People: 
Missouri (724) 

Adrian Peterson is active for the Minnesota Vikings against Detroit after being listed as questionable because of an illness. 
In Kansas City, Steelers quarterback Landry Jones is making his first NFL start because Ben Roethlisberger and Michael Vick are inactive. Chiefs wide receiver Jeremy Maclin is inactive because of a concussion. 
Roethlisberger is out with a knee injury for the fourth straight game and Vick is out with a hamstring injury. Jones threw two second-half touchdown passes to Martavis Bryant last week after Vick was injured in a win over Arizona. 
In New England, running back Dion Lewis is inactive because of an abdominal injury, but receiver Brandon LaFell is active for the first time this season after missing five games because of a foot injury.
